The paper deals with activity recognition in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach that involves learning a policy for dynamic feature prioritization, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with streaming video, which involves real-time processing and transmission of data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves feature selection and prioritization, which is a common problem in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
